# Bitwarden Secrets Manager — project UUID for cta-app.
#
# This file is NOT a secret. Secrets Manager project IDs are non-sensitive
# identifiers and are safe to commit. The ACCESS TOKEN is the secret; it lives
# in the Windows Credential Manager (generic target "bws_access_token"), never
# in this repo. See scripts/bws-exec.sh and the SECRETS POLICY in CLAUDE.md.
#
# SETUP (Joe): after you create the machine account + project in the Bitwarden
# web vault, paste the project's UUID on its own line below (uncommented), e.g.
#
#     00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
#
# bws-exec.sh reads the first non-comment, non-blank line as BWS_PROJECT_ID,
# or you may override per-invocation with the BWS_PROJECT_ID env var.
#
# Secrets Manager project UUID for the cta-app mobile repo (Expo/EAS secrets).
ac76651c-c42c-4f49-abd6-b468010fbdec
